      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) derived from the Giersiepen power-law model applied to CFD-predicted shear stress and exposure time. NIH is the accepted regulatory metric for CPB hemolysis assessment (FDA guidance 2017). Secondary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH (ratio to predicate device NIH). Both QoIs are directly relevant to the clinical decision. Achieves Gradation 2.",
