      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the identical FDA GCBP geometry using blood-analogue fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity matched) and porcine blood for hemolysis tests. All 25 CFD runs and 18 bench experiments fall within the declared operating envelope (1–7 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM, tip clearance 0.10–0.30 mm). Dense coverage of the envelope including all four corner points and the nominal centre. Achieves Gradation 3: validation on identical geometry and fluid under conditions spanning the full declared envelope.",
